<h3>The API</h3>
<p>Uses This provides a very simple API, based on the <a href="http://jsonapi.org/format/" title="The JSON API specification.">JSON API spec</a>. Since it's 100% static, all requests are GET requests. I'd love to know if you do something interesting with it!</p>

<h4 id="interviews-endpoints">Interviews</h4>

<h5 id="interviews-list">Getting a list</h5>
<p class="summary">This method returns a paginated list of all the interviews.</p>
<p><a href="/api/interviews" title="Request a list of all the interviews as JSON.">https://usesthis.com/api/interviews</a></p>
<pre>
<%= File.read(File.join(@site.output_paths[:site], 'api', 'interviews', 'index.json')) %>
</pre>

<h5 id="interviews-interview">Getting an interview</h5>
<p class="summary">This method returns a complete interview for the given slug.</p>
<p><a href="/api/interviews/<%= @site.latest_post.slug %>" title="Request a given interview as JSON.">https://usesthis.com/api/interviews/{slug}</a></p>
<pre>
<%= File.read(File.join(@site.output_paths[:site], 'api', 'interviews', @site.latest_post.slug, 'index.json')) %>
</pre>

